Oak is a middleware framework for Deno used to build web applications and APIs â€” similar to Express.js in Node.js.

....................................
What is Oak?
...................................

Oak is:

1. A middleware-based web framework for Deno.
2. Built on top of Deno's native HTTP server.
3. Inspired by Koa (Node.js).
4. Designed to be modular, modern, and async/await-friendly.

..............................................................................
Oak is imported directly from a URL (Deno uses ES modules, not npm):
..............................................................................

import { Application } from "https://deno.land/x/oak@v12.6.1/mod.ts";
